  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">HWRPB Key/Value Offset Map</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">This page documents the kKeyValue offset map for the HWRPB (Hardware Restart Parameter Block) and its chained structures, as encoded in deviceLib/Hwrpb.h. It is a navigation aid; the authoritative layout is the AARM Section III "Common Architecture, Console Interface" (Table 26-1 header, Table 26-4 per-CPU slot), cross-referenced against the read-only apisrm/srmapi SSOT and the live DS20 SRM dump. EmulatR is the only tree edited; apisrm/srmapi is never modified.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="SeeAlso">See Also.</text> journals/HWRPB_PerCpuSlot_FieldMap_AARM_20260629.md (the full AARM-vs-Hwrpb.h reconciliation), journals/HWRPB_Region_Fidelity_and_Resume_20260624.md (region methodology).</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">The kKeyValue pattern</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Each HWRPB field has a convenience constexpr "key = value" constant (value is the field's byte offset from its region base), in the same spirit as kAlphaPageSize. A field can then be reached two equivalent ways: by typed struct member, or by offset key over a raw byte window through a View union. The two paths are pinned together by static_asserts so they can never silently drift.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">// offset keys (constexpr uint64_t, like kAlphaPageSize = 8192)</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">constexpr uint64_t kSlotStateFlags       = 0x080;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">constexpr uint64_t kSlotCycleCounterFreq = 0x270;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">constexpr uint64_t kSlotSize             = 0x280;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">// View union: overlay a raw byte window with the typed struct</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">union PerCpuSlotView { uint8_t raw[kSlotSize]; PerCpuSlot fields; };</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">// typed-member path and offset-key path are equivalent:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">uint64_t a = view.fields.state.raw;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">uint64_t b = peek&lt;uint64_t&gt;(view.raw, kSlotStateFlags);   // a == b</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">poke&lt;uint64_t&gt;(hdrBase, kHwrpbSystemVariation, 0x1805); // DS20 SYSVAR</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">peek/poke are memcpy-based, so they are alignment- and strict-aliasing-safe wherever the base points in guest memory. Host (x86_64) and guest (Alpha) are both little-endian and the structs are #pragma pack(1), so the overlay is byte-faithful.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
