    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="" style="font-weight:bold;">Note (PALCODE REVISION):</text> the AARM defines +168 as one bit-packed quadword (bits 63:48 max processors sharing this PALcode, 47:32 compatibility, 23:16 variation, 15:8 major, 7:0 minor). EmulatR keeps a pal_rev/pal_var u32 split at 0x0A8/0x0AC: the offset is correct, but the high 32 bits (max-procs + compat) are not separately modeled. Widen when the PAL-rev publishing path is reworked.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="" style="font-weight:bold;">Note (REASON FOR HALT):</text> the AARM halt codes (0 boot, 1 operator crash, 2 kstack-not-valid, 3 invalid SCBB, 4 invalid PTBR, 5 CALL_PAL HALT in kernel, 6 double-error, 7 machine-check in PALcode) do not match EmulatR's HaltCode enum numbering. Reconcile before relying on the halt reason cross-process.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">DSRDB section offset keys</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The DSRDB (Dynamic System Recognition Data Block) is a separate top-level HWRPB section reached via kHwrpbDsrdbOffset (+312), found live on DS20 at PA 0x2ac0. It is NOT part of the per-CPU slot (it was incorrectly embedded there before 2026-06-29). Validate this layout field-by-field against the live 0x2ac0 dump before relying on it.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="9" colcount="3" style="border-width:0px; border-spacing:0px; border-collapse:collapse; cell-border-width:1px; border-color:#000000; border-style:solid; head-row-background-color:#00ffff; alt-row-background-color:none;">
      <thead style="vertical-align:top">
        <td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">Key</text></para></td>
        <td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">Offset</text></para></td>
        <td><para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">Field</text></para></td>
      </thead>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">kDsrdbSmm</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">0x00</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">system marketing-model code</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">kDsrdbLurtOffset</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">0x08</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">offset to LURT table</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">kDsrdbNameOffset</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">0x10</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">offset to system name</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">kDsrdbLurtCount</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">0x18</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">number of LURT entries</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">kDsrdbLurtTable</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">0x20</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">LURT table (20 qwords)</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">kDsrdbNameCount</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">0xC0</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">length of system name</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">kDsrdbName</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">0xC8</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">system name (7 qwords)</para></td></tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top"><td><para styleclass="Normal">kDsrdbSize</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">0x100</para></td><td><para styleclass="Normal">DSRDB size (256 bytes)</para></td></tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Correctness: keys pinned to struct offsets</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">A block of static_asserts at the end of Hwrpb.h ties each key to the matching offsetof() in its struct, so the typed-member path and the offset-key path can never silently diverge as the layout evolves:</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">static_assert(kSlotCycleCounterFreq == offsetof(PerCpuSlot, cycle_count_freq), "key/cycle_count_freq");</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">static_assert(kHwrpbSystemVariation == offsetof(HwrpbHeader, system_variation), "key/sysvar");</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Verified with g++ -std=c++17: the header compiles clean and every static_assert passes (PerCpuSlot = 0x280, HwrpbHeader = 320, Dsrdb = 0x100, cycle_count_freq at 0x270).</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
